</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="15815850728A89148B38CB5BEF02CCC0" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="type species">
<paragraph id="BEF2844C48B1AE4D1326D572E0F93579" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Type species by original designation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F6D2CB15CCEC4D9756B30851F722192" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName id="BF9985B3A4002463B7962A6DA7D7B9DE" authorityName="Davis &amp; Kuo" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia daliensis" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="daliensis">
<emphasis id="86816F6897BDF31B2D45912C1A380D8F" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Erhaia daliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Davis &amp; Kuo, in 
<bibRefCitation id="4C21040D5ECE916FB2E40B2BA5B7185D" author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="48 - 78" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" refId="B2" refString="Davis, GM, Kuo, Y-H, Hoagland, KE, Chen, P-L, Yang, H-M, Chen, D-J, 1985. Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 137: 48 - 78, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" title="Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" volume="137" year="1985">Davis et al. 1985</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9893A1F1E563B5332AFFDF317B098013" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="shells">
<paragraph id="C91618A0C9A7D87981B33B949E00DA32" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Shells.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="373DA80193745808A0D97A25DF9374B8" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The shells vary from conical to more or less ovoid, rarely with a flaring final part of the body whorl. The apex is flattened as in the European amnicolid genus Bythinella Moquin-Tandon, 1856, because of the very low spiral of the protoconch. The peristome is continuous and may be more or less protruding. The parietal and the columellar side of the aperture are about equally long and the regularly curved palatal side of the aperture gradually passes into the basal side, forming a single, regularly curved border. Bythinella cannot be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="DBB972464389F996A5C1D62540F88044" authorityName="Davis &amp; Kuo" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Erhaia</taxonomicName>
conchologically, but in some 
<taxonomicName id="0D8668EB8202910C2307EB9997F03E24" authorityName="Davis &amp; Kuo" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Erhaia</taxonomicName>
species from China the columella has one or two spiral lamellae, that are not known from Bythinella. In 
<taxonomicName id="5DC74DAB793AD1DA78341B7179996B2E" authorityName="Davis &amp; Kuo" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Erhaia</taxonomicName>
the protoconch may have spiral striae, which have not been described for any of the Bythinella species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4D1D7F0FA33F6445C34400B499A30B38" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4FE2BFD2B8848B63C30203ADA135BF1D" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="282650D6EE852D778270A684FED02EB3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="189B35E8507EB238C479EA2579EA0D1A" authorityName="Davis &amp; Kuo" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Erhaia</taxonomicName>
is mainly known from China, where it has been recorded with various species from the province of Yunnan in the west to the provinces of Hunan, Hubei and Fujian in the east (
<bibRefCitation id="00AAFC76E2F8C1BF5966F71D63CBBCD5" author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="48 - 78" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" refId="B2" refString="Davis, GM, Kuo, Y-H, Hoagland, KE, Chen, P-L, Yang, H-M, Chen, D-J, 1985. Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 137: 48 - 78, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" title="Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" volume="137" year="1985">Davis et al. 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F109ADCFF9F6FF5D2B178A854C93ECF9" author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="391 - 427" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065020" refId="B4" refString="Davis, GM, Kang, ZB, 1995. Advances in the Systematics of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) from the People's Republic of China. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 146: 391 - 427, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065020" title="Advances in the Systematics of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) from the People's Republic of China." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065020" volume="146" year="1995">Davis and Kang 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B1E6EC09088CD68C584521F11E928829" author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="273 - 299" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" refId="B5" refString="Davis, GM, Rao, S, 1997. Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 148: 273 - 299, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" title="Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" volume="148" year="1997">Davis and Rao 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="CAD055B14845DBD6CB31C932C70C63EE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.4269/ajtmh.2000.62.453" author="Wilke, T" journalOrPublisher="The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="453 - 459" refId="B19" refString="Wilke, T, Davis, GM, Gong, X, Liu, H-X, 2000. Erhaia (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): phylogenetic relationships and the question of Paragonimus coevolution in Asia. The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene 62: 453 - 459, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4269/ajtmh.2000.62.453" title="Erhaia (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): phylogenetic relationships and the question of Paragonimus coevolution in Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.4269/ajtmh.2000.62.453" volume="62" year="2000">Wilke et al. 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="75450CB4CE5B73D56A581BA314D1C805" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1635/0097-3157(2001)151[0001:MSOHMG]2.0.CO;2" author="Wilke, T" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Biology" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="B18" refString="Wilke, T, Davis, GM, Falniowski, A, Giusti, F, Bodon, M, Szarowska, M, 2001. Molecular systematics of Hydrobiidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Rissooidea): testing monophyly and phylogenetic relationships. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 151: 1-21. https://doi.org/10.1635/0097-3157(2001)151[0001:MSOHMG]2.0.CO;2" title="Molecular systematics of Hydrobiidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Rissooidea): testing monophyly and phylogenetic relationships. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 151: 1 - 21." url="https://doi.org/10.1635/0097-3157(2001)151[0001:MSOHMG]2.0.CO;2" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="06F37F7F138515F064D2F8DD33C14A95" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-14-29" author="Liu, L" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Biology and Evolution" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="B12" refString="Liu, L, Huo, G-N, He, H-B, Zhou, B, Attwood, SW, 2014. A phylogeny for the Pomatiopsidae (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): a resource for taxonomic, parasitological and biodiversity studies. BMC Evolutionary Biology 14: 29. https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-14-29" title="A phylogeny for the Pomatiopsidae (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): a resource for taxonomic, parasitological and biodiversity studies. BMC Evolutionary Biology 14: 29." url="https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-14-29" year="2014">Liu et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). One species was described from northern India (
<bibRefCitation id="9A39D50CB0D8029ABAEF1BB518EE4223" author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="273 - 299" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" refId="B5" refString="Davis, GM, Rao, S, 1997. Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 148: 273 - 299, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" title="Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" volume="148" year="1997">Davis and Rao 1997</bibRefCitation>
), three from Nepal (
<bibRefCitation id="BB307EA0E3A2FC29B2DE4F4C83CB0A73" author="Nesemann, H" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Biology and Evolution" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="B13" refString="Nesemann, H, Sharma, S, Sharma, G, Khanal, SN, Pradhan, B, Shah, DN, Tachamo, RD, 2007. Class Gastropoda. In: Nesemann H, Sharma S, Sharma G, Khanal SN, Pradhan B, Shah DN, Tachamo RD (Eds) Aquatic Invertebrates of the Ganga River System, Volume 1: Mollusca, Annelida, Crustacea (in part): 57-102." title="Class Gastropoda. In: Nesemann H, Sharma S, Sharma G, Khanal SN, Pradhan B, Shah DN, Tachamo RD (Eds) Aquatic Invertebrates of the Ganga River System, Volume 1: Mollusca, Annelida, Crustacea (in part): 57 - 102." year="2007">Nesemann et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
) and one from Bhutan (
<bibRefCitation id="AC9F561E193FAF744A88E6539C141BAC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.679.13326" author="Gittenberger, E" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="21 - 28" refId="B7" refString="Gittenberger, E, Sherub, S, Stelbrink, B, 2017a. Erhaia Davis &amp; Kuo (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae) also in Bhutan. ZooKeys 679: 21 - 28, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.679.13326" title="Erhaia Davis &amp; Kuo (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae) also in Bhutan." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.679.13326" volume="679" year="2017 a">Gittenberger et al. 2017a</bibRefCitation>
). Here we deal with the systematics of only the species occurring in the southern Himalayan foothills in Bhutan, India, and Nepal.
</paragraph>
